<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 04 at 11:56PM EDT  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...Heavy Rain to Push North Overnight...
While widespread rain will persist through much of the night...the
heavy rain that has measured up to an inch and a half through
midnight over parts of Orleans and particularly Niagara county
will push north over the lake.
The heaviest rains through 1 AM will be over the northern half of
Niagara county where an additional half to one inch of rain could
fall. Motorists traveling through these counties should be alert
for significant ponding on roadways. There may also be some poor
drainage flooding in low areas.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways...particularly
through moving water!</description>
